Problem_with_redundant_assumption:
Assumption:
Assumption 1: $n$ is a non-negative integer,
Assumption 2: The Fibonacci sequence is defined by $F_0 = 0$, $F_1 = 1$,
Assumption 3: For $n \geq 2$, $F_n = F_{n-1} + F_{n-2}$.
Assumption 4: $$A^{n+1}=A\,A^n=\begin{pmatrix}
1 & 1 \\ 1 & 0
\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}
F_{n+1} & F_{n} \\ F_{n} & F_{n-1}
\end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix}
F_{n+1}+F_n & F_{n}+F_{n-1} \\  F_{n+1} & F_{n}
\end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix}
F_{n+2} & F_{n+1} \\ F_{n+1} & F_{n}
\end{pmatrix}$$
